@startuml state_operation_lifecycle
!include ../../../design/theme.iuml

mainframe **state** Operation Lifecycle

[*] --> Running : New(type, parentID)\nID generated, StartTime set

state Running {
    Running : Context bag enrichable
    Running : Enrich() / EnrichMany()
    Running : Operation hooks fire (Phase 2)
    Running : Work executes
}

Running --> Completed : Complete()\nEndTime set
Running --> Failed : Fail(reason)\nEndTime set, FailReason set

state Completed {
    Completed : Duration = EndTime - StartTime
    Completed : Removed from Tracker
    Completed : operation.complete event emitted
}

state Failed {
    Failed : Duration = EndTime - StartTime
    Failed : FailReason available
    Failed : Removed from Tracker
    Failed : operation.complete event (status=failed)
}

Completed --> [*]
Failed --> [*]

note right of Running
  **Context enrichment sources:**
  1. Server: _start_ns, _operation_id
  2. REX metadata: shared.rex.*
  3. Operation hooks: plugins enrich synchronously
  4. Command hooks: pre-hook context_values

  All enrichment happens during Running state.
  Context is frozen after Complete/Fail.
end note

@enduml
